author: Rudy Setiono
title: Extracting M-of-N Rules from Trained Neural Networks
venue: School of Computing National University of Singapore
window: M-of-N rule extraction algorithm. This problem has been used by Towell and Shavlik [3] to test their algorithms which extract symbolic rules from knowledge based neural networks. Each sample in the dataset is described by a 60-nucleotide-long DNA sequence. A nucleotide may assume one of the 4 possible values: G (Guanine), T (Thymine), C (Cytosine), or A (Adenine).
